.TH "SPEECHRECOGNITIONRESULT.LENGTH" "3JS" "September 30, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
SpeechRecognitionResult.length \- SpeechRecognitionResult: length
property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]length\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]SpeechRecognitionResult\f[R] interface returns the length of the
\(lqarray\(rq \(em the number of \f[CR]SpeechRecognitionAlternative\f[R]
objects contained in the result (also referred to as \(lqn\-best
alternatives\(rq.)
.PP
The number of alternatives contained in the result depends on what the
\f[CR]SpeechRecognition.maxAlternatives\f[R] property was set to when
the speech recognition was first initiated.
.SH VALUE
A number.
.SH EXAMPLES
This code is excerpted from our \c
.UR https://github.com/mdn/dom-examples/blob/main/web-speech-api/speech-color-changer/script.js
Speech color changer
.UE \c
\ example.
.IP
.EX
recognition.onresult = (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  \f[B]const\f[R] color = event.results[0][0].transcript;
  diagnostic.textContent = \(gaResult received: ${color}.\(ga;
  bg.style.backgroundColor = color;

  console.log(event.results[0].length);
};
.EE
